	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey.<br><br>I spent a loooong time camping this girl, to get a book for a friend about four weeks ago.  (Beginning of October - Torvonnilous server.)  Certainly at this time, her recycle time was very consistently about twenty minutes.<br><br>Certainly what you said about the dungeon being empty is very true.  I killed her about ten times, before I got the book and during this time she dropped the robe about five times.  (KIlled a PH about the same number of times.  Would guess it's a close to 50/50 ratio for her and her PH.)<br><br>Every time I yelled if anyone wanted to come and get a robe and only twice did anyone come for it.  (If someone wanted it and was too small, I'd have even run it out to them, but there's just no-one about.)  Damn shame to see even a mildly nice piece of gear like this just rot away.<br><br>The dark elf parts certainly drop off the other DE's in Najena and can be used to make Blackened Teir'Dal, which isn't too bad, as far as stat boosting foods go.  I have a coupla stacks in the bank, which I plan on handing out to DE's, whenever they make comments about my Iksar looking hungry.  Hah!<br><br>AlAaraaf.<br>"Death is coming..."<br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
